<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph continue="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molineri &amp; Dias &amp; Zúñiga" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tortopus coreguaje" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreguaje">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tortopus coreguaje</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, known from male imago and nymph, can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by the following combination of characters: In male imagos, 1) fore wing length 10.9-11.0 mm (male); 2) pale wings, veins translucent gray; 3) pedestal short with relatively large, straight and very long parastyli (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56-57</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">67</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">69</figureCitation>
) (parastylus 2.6 times the length of pedestal base, in lateral view the parastylus reach 0.37 of the length of forceps from base); 3) ventral knob on forceps base relatively small; 4) penis relatively thin at base (fused portion), not strongly expanded distally (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">67</figureCitation>
); and 5) relatively dark species, head shaded stronger between lateral ocelli, occiput shaded gray except on pale medial line (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). In the nymph: 1) inner protuberances on mandibular tusk almost contiguous (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">59-61</figureCitation>
); 2) frontal tuft of setae with irregular sinuous form (arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">58</figureCitation>
); 3) ventral and dorsal projection at the apex of fore tarsus subequal in length (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">63</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Male imago</emphasis>
. Length (mm): body, 11.0; fore wing, 10.9-11.0; hind wing, 4.8; cerci, 28.0. General coloration yellowish white shaded with gray (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). Head. Coloration yellowish white shaded widely with gray on dorsum, shaded stronger between lateral ocelli, except around median ocellus and hind margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). Antennae: scape and pedicel yellowish white completely shaded with gray, flagellum hyaline. Thorax. Pronotum with anterior ring hyaline, shaded with black posterolaterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
); posterior ring shaded gray except on sublateral areas and medial line. Mesonotum whitish yellow shaded with gray along medioparapsidal sutures and shaded with black on a V-shaped mark between posterior scutal protuberances (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). Metanotum whitish yellow shaded gray medially. Thoracic pleura and sterna whitish yellow, with grayish small marks medially on furcasterna. Legs yellowish white shaded with grayish (fore legs broken off and lost). Wings: Membrane hyaline except basally slightly grayish, longitudinal and cross veins translucent shaded slightly with gray. Abdomen. Abdominal segments translucent-hyaline. Tergum I shaded gray anterolaterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
), terga II-IX shaded more extensively towards rear segments, except on: medial line of terga II-VII, and two pale marks (one submedian and one sublateral) in II-IX; tergum X shaded more completely with gray. Abdominal sterna shaded widely with brownish gray except on intersegmental membranes and around gill sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">66</figureCitation>
). Genitalia (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56-57</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">67-69</figureCitation>
): sternum IX shaded with black on posterior margin and at both sides of the median furrow; relatively large parastyli orangeish, straight and long (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56</figureCitation>
); parastylus 2.6 times the length of pedestal base, in lateral view the parastylus reach 0.37 of the length of forceps from base; forceps and penis yellowish white, shaded gray on forceps. Caudal filament whitish translucent.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" start="Figures 56–64" startId="F9">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Figures 56-64.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molineri &amp; Dias &amp; Zúñiga" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tortopus coreguaje" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreguaje">
