</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Male nymph</emphasis>
(immature). Length: body, 9.5 mm; cerci, 2.5 mm; caudal filament, 2.0 mm. General coloration whitish shaded with gray (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">70</figureCitation>
). Head. Head shaded with gray in net-shaped pattern posteriorly to epicranial suture (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">70</figureCitation>
); anteriorly to this suture with two small lateral irregular-sinuous-shaped tufts of short setae (anterior to lateral ocelli, arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">58</figureCitation>
); frontal ridge relatively straight in dorsal view (Fig. 
